Political economists Beaumier and Cartwright point out, ‘no one country dominates all three phases of semiconductor production,’ allowing different nations to ‘wield influence across design, and manufacturing.’ Currently, AI design is centralised in the US while AI regulation is most heavily associated with European Governance frameworks. Further, the manufacturing is largely dependent on Taiwan and South Korea, whose large- scale fabrication plants place East Asia as central to the world’s AI Hardware development.

This structural dissonance leaves the global market in a complicated position.

